		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Covariance matrix</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>In <a href="/wiki/Statistics" title="Statistics">statistics</a> and <a href="/wiki/Probability_theory" title="Probability theory">probability theory</a>, the <b>covariance matrix</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Matrix_(mathematics)" title="Matrix (mathematics)">matrix</a> of <a href="/wiki/Covariance" title="Covariance">covariances</a> between elements of a vector. It is the natural generalization to higher dimensions of the concept of the <a href="/wiki/Variance" title="Variance">variance</a> of a <a href="/wiki/Scalar_(mathematics)" title="Scalar (mathematics)">scalar</a>-valued <a href="/wiki/Random_variable" title="Random variable">random variable</a>.</p>
